3
00:02:34,180 --> 00:02:36,700
Whitebeard's era is over.

4
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:41,110
Burning ambition spurs pirates
the world over into action.

5
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:45,010
And then there's Trafalgar Law...

6
00:02:45,010 --> 00:02:47,630
What? We're still not going?

7
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:49,920
Let's just go to the New World already!

8
00:02:50,820 --> 00:02:53,970
I told you, we're waiting for the right time.

9
00:02:53,970 --> 00:02:55,250
Don't rush things.

10
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:58,890
The great treasure, One Piece, isn't going anywhere.

11
00:02:58,890 --> 00:03:03,250
But you know, Blackbeard and his group
are causing a stir in the New World!

12
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:07,830
Rumor has it that they've
already crushed one pirate crew!

13
00:03:07,830 --> 00:03:13,040
These 100-million-bounty rookies are streaming
into the New World to snag a spot as an Emperor!

14
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:17,910
If we keep hanging back here,
we're gonna fall behind, Captain!

15
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:21,960
It's better for us if they're
trying to destroy one another.

16
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:24,440
We won't get involved in those petty fights.

17
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:29,690
Quit whining and just follow my orders.

18
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:32,860
When the time is right,
we'll rise to the top.

19
00:03:32,860 --> 00:03:34,390
Captain!

20
00:03:34,390 --> 00:03:36,290
We'll follow you anywhere!

21
00:03:36,290 --> 00:03:38,730
Aye aye, Captain!

22
00:03:42,570 --> 00:03:48,010
Kaido, one of the Four Emperors,
highly favors this island base.

23
00:03:48,010 --> 00:03:50,480
And I'm in charge of security here.

24
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:53,080
And? What do you want me to do?

25
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:57,460
I'm not telling you to do anything.
It's just a warning.

26
00:03:57,460 --> 00:04:01,770
You're better off not angering Kaido, rookie.

27
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:06,480
In other words, if I take your head,
then Kaido will come for mine?

28
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:09,760
Now he gets it! If so, then you can–

29
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,830
That simplifies the matter!

30
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:18,170
An ancient zoan type, huh? Now, that's rare!

31
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:28,250
Scratch...

32
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,900
Boom!

33
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:40,490
\h\h\hThere're quite a few left...!

34
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:42,390
\h\h\hWe really stepped in it...

35
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:44,300
Ouch...

36
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:48,900
Don't worry, guys! We've got
Captain Apoo on our side!

37
00:04:49,540 --> 00:04:50,960
Listen up, men!

38
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:52,110
– Aye!
– Aye!

39
00:04:52,110 --> 00:04:53,140
Make a run for it!

40
00:04:53,140 --> 00:04:54,610
– What?!
– What?!

41
00:04:56,070 --> 00:05:00,030
There's no winning against
a herd of those wild boars!

42
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:05,550
Captain! We're headed straight for a cliff!

43
00:05:05,550 --> 00:05:07,350
It's our best bet for escape!

44
00:05:08,860 --> 00:05:10,910
Oh no! We're done for!

45
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:11,990
Don't give up!

46
00:05:11,990 --> 00:05:14,590
But the ocean's right beneath that cliff!

47
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:16,790
Who cares?! Jump!

48
00:05:16,790 --> 00:05:19,340
– What?!
– What?!

49
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:20,300
What the...?!

50
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:23,700
Captain! I don't know if you noticed,
but we're running on air!

51
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:26,340
The boars are following us into the air too!

52
00:05:26,340 --> 00:05:28,340
I can see that!

53
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:32,480
What the hell is with this island?!

54
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:36,650
It's so hot...

55
00:05:37,130 --> 00:05:39,950
My legs can't take it anymore.

56
00:05:39,950 --> 00:05:42,930
There's no strength in my body either...

57
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:45,920
Ouch. A fish just bit me.

58
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,890
Quit your bellyaching, Wolf!

59
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:52,260
Our raft almost broke because of you.

60
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:54,480
That's why we're in this situation.

61
00:05:54,480 --> 00:06:00,710
Trying to sail the seas of the New World
on that raft was an absurd idea anyway.

62
00:06:01,410 --> 00:06:05,980
We should've stolen a warship back at Marineford!

63
00:06:05,980 --> 00:06:09,650
We had grown attached to that raft, though.

64
00:06:09,650 --> 00:06:14,150
You guys don't prepare for anything.

65
00:06:14,150 --> 00:06:16,190
Put me in command!

66
00:06:16,190 --> 00:06:18,990
I'll take over as captain for you, Teach.

67
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:22,130
Don't make me kill you.

68
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:24,260
We're the Blackbeard Pirates.

69
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:28,940
Heaven already knows the fate of all.

70
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,710
We're running low on booze.

71
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:36,670
Can't we go to an island with a town?

72
00:06:38,530 --> 00:06:39,610
I agree.

73
00:06:39,610 --> 00:06:42,480
But forget the ship; I need some nicer clothes.

74
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:44,680
I'm so sick of these prison clothes.

75
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,550
I'll go take a look.

76
00:06:46,550 --> 00:06:48,750
They're taking too long.

77
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:53,530
No argument here. But these guys
sure look to be going numb.

78
00:06:56,890 --> 00:06:57,830
Ain't that right...

79
00:06:57,830 --> 00:07:00,570
Jewelry Bonney?

80
00:07:00,570 --> 00:07:03,140
Captain Bonney...

81
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:12,080
I'm impressed that a young lady like yourself
managed to get a bounty of over 100 million!

82
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:16,010
The New World is best left to the strong.

83
00:07:16,010 --> 00:07:19,300
You did well making it
this far from the South Blue,

84
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:22,000
but this is the last stop on your voyage.

85
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:30,190
I don't need a weakling like you on my crew.

86
00:07:30,190 --> 00:07:34,630
However, if you become my woman,
I'll gladly take you along.

87
00:07:35,930 --> 00:07:38,880
Come see the waters ahead. Huh?

88
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:41,670
Screw you, you bearded pig!

89
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:46,140
Seems you've been rejected.

90
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:49,540
Forget it! You're one crude bitch!

91
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:51,850
A woman should be classy, after all!

92
00:07:51,850 --> 00:07:55,150
I've already got all the ruffians
I need on my crew!

93
00:07:55,150 --> 00:07:57,720
Yeah, you tell her!

94
00:07:59,490 --> 00:08:02,930
We'll stick to the plan where
we hand you off to the Marines

95
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:05,730
in exchange for a proper warship!

96
00:08:05,730 --> 00:08:07,030
Captain.

97
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:07,050
Huh?

98
00:08:07,050 --> 00:08:08,830
I can see the Marines.

99
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:11,890
They've got the warship
they promised us, right?!

100
00:08:11,890 --> 00:08:14,840
There's indeed a ship,
but I doubt it's intended for us.

101
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:17,310
Huh? How can you tell?

102
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:20,950
Akainu is on board.

103
00:08:20,950 --> 00:08:24,550
Damn! This just got too rich for me!

104
00:08:24,550 --> 00:08:26,620
Let's get the hell outta here!

105
00:08:28,510 --> 00:08:30,460
A complete failure!

106
00:08:33,690 --> 00:08:35,570
Where's Blackbeard?

107
00:08:35,570 --> 00:08:37,100
He's gone!

108
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:40,620
When I heard you'd fled from the government,

109
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:42,500
my blood ran cold.

110
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:46,910
But it's all over now.

111
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:51,810
You bastards are gonna pay!

112
00:08:58,450 --> 00:08:59,650
He vanished?!

113
00:08:59,650 --> 00:09:02,850
Yup, that's the honest truth.

114
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:07,230
Whose idea was this?! Sengoku's?!

115
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:11,260
No... Even higher than that.

116
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:18,570
And I'm not talking in metaphors.
Literally, he was gone like "poof"!

117
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:23,740
It surprised me. I had no idea that
the Shadow-Shadow Fruit could do that.

118
00:09:23,740 --> 00:09:25,340
This is no laughing matter!

119
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:29,710
It's fine. He was on the verge of death.

120
00:09:29,710 --> 00:09:32,150
There's nothing he can do now.

121
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:36,890
Unless he somehow turned himself
into a zombie, you know?

122
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:39,030
That sure would suit him, after all.

123
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:41,590
You're too nonchalant
about your sloppy work!

124
00:09:42,860 --> 00:09:45,730
Don't get so cocky with me!

125
00:09:45,730 --> 00:09:48,900
When, exactly, did you become my boss?!

126
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:54,070
No matter how far up the government
ladder you've climbed, I'm a pirate.

127
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:55,370
So I don't care!

128
00:09:56,810 --> 00:10:03,180
The moment I lose interest in our little deal,
I'll just drop out of the Seven Warlords!

129
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:06,040
Don't ever forget that.

130
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:12,890
M-Mister Tanuki!

131
00:10:12,890 --> 00:10:15,050
We tell you come back anytime,

132
00:10:15,060 --> 00:10:17,160
but this too soon, right?

133
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:19,610
No, you've got the wrong man!

134
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:23,940
I may look like him, but I'm
actually his friend, Chopper Mask!

135
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:26,020
You trying too hard, Mister Tanuki.

136
00:10:26,020 --> 00:10:30,020
You use disguise to hide being
embarrassed when coming back so soon?

137
00:10:30,020 --> 00:10:32,240
That's not it at all! I'm–

138
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:38,320
Mister Tanuki okay?

139
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:42,320
All being very mean.

140
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:45,020
In situation like this, must play along.

141
00:10:45,590 --> 00:10:47,890
Fine, you win!
Your kindness got to me!

142
00:10:47,890 --> 00:10:49,530
Oh, Mister Tanuki!

143
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,270
That tickles, you jerk!

144
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:11,590
Truth be told, something came up.
Mind if I stay a bit longer?

145
00:11:11,590 --> 00:11:15,220
No worry! You very welcome here.

146
00:11:15,790 --> 00:11:21,500
There are so many plants growing
on that tree that I've never seen before.

147
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,830
Please let me study them!

148
00:11:23,830 --> 00:11:27,330
In that case, we have perfect place.

149
00:11:27,330 --> 00:11:30,900
Also, I need to become
stronger and more capable.

150
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,370
No time to waste.

151
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:36,050
Oh, Mister Tanuki? Back already?

152
00:11:36,050 --> 00:11:37,680
This great!

153
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:42,380
Everyone, I'll be staying on this island
for a while, so let's get along!

154
00:11:42,380 --> 00:11:44,950
Right, this is place.

155
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,660
What is this?

156
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:49,150
This be...

157
00:11:58,890 --> 00:12:01,200
village library.

158
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,240
Use for research.

159
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,900
Look at all the books!

160
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:09,510
There're so many,
all the way from front to back!

161
00:12:11,310 --> 00:12:12,540
Incredible!

162
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:17,380
They're all books about the plants I want
to research and the medicines I want to make!

163
00:12:17,380 --> 00:12:19,940
There's no end to them!

164
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:23,650
On island, many plants make strong medicine.

165
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:30,260
Our technology make medicine, but birds
always keep ingredients away from people.

166
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:32,630
Was big problem for all.

167
00:12:32,630 --> 00:12:36,500
I misjudged these islanders
due to their appearance,

168
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:40,440
but now that I think about it,
their weapons are really advanced.

169
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,870
They all resembled primitive savages,

170
00:12:42,870 --> 00:12:47,400
but the science here is actually far along!

171
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,010
There's so much to learn here!

172
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:50,450
Mister Tanuki!

173
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:54,810
Maybe think you say all in head,
 but every word Mister Tanuki say out loud.

174
00:12:54,810 --> 00:12:56,790
And very rude too!

175
00:12:56,790 --> 00:13:01,190
This country... I wonder how much
I can do while I'm here!

176
00:13:03,310 --> 00:13:04,660
It's a yeti!

177
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:05,810
Shoot it dead!

178
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:06,960
Don't let it get away!

179
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,470
Take it down!

180
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:11,110
Pirates are incredible!

181
00:13:11,110 --> 00:13:14,290
There are countless people like that out at sea!

182
00:13:14,290 --> 00:13:17,100
Chopper, go out to sea some day.

183
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:21,460
If you do, you'll realize just how
small your own problems are.

184
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:26,530
Compared to the rest of the world,
your home island is this small!

185
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:27,570
Really?

186
00:13:27,570 --> 00:13:31,390
No, it's smaller! Like this! It's true!

187
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,960
I'm not even a human!

188
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,600
I'm a monster!

189
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:43,520
I can't join your crew!

190
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:44,550
So...!

191
00:13:45,470 --> 00:13:47,080
So I just came to say thank you...

192
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,680
I really appreciate you guys.

193
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:55,790
Thank you for asking me to join you.

194
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:58,980
I'll stay here, but...

195
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:03,090
one day, if you feel like it, stop by agai–

196
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:04,190
Shut up!

197
00:14:04,190 --> 00:14:06,820
Let's go!

198
00:14:19,690 --> 00:14:22,140
Ever since Luffy brought me out to sea,

199
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:25,110
it's been a struggle just to keep up.

200
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:28,110
How can I contribute more, Luffy?

201
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:38,420
I never want to experience
anything like that again.

202
00:14:39,590 --> 00:14:40,490
But...

203
00:14:41,060 --> 00:14:42,150
back then...

204
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:56,210
Luffy... was probably
in more pain than any of us!

205
00:14:58,980 --> 00:15:01,440
Because you made me
one of your crewmates...

206
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:05,580
I've been just fine, not caring
what others thought about me.

207
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:14,250
If it means I can be of any help to you...

208
00:15:15,820 --> 00:15:19,400
then I'll even become a real monster!

209
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,430
Chopper!

210
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:23,330
Chopper!

211
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,700
Chopper!

212
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:36,310
Luffy!

213
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:37,720
I...

214
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,170
will definitely...

215
00:15:39,170 --> 00:15:42,470
become stronger!

216
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:48,360
The Kamabakka Queendom
on the Grand Line....

217
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:52,160
Vhaat exactly did you see in that article?

218
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:53,740
I read you loud and clear...

219
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:56,370
You calmed down so suddenly...

220
00:15:56,370 --> 00:16:03,840
That article contained a message from Luffy
that only his crewmates would understand.

221
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:08,080
But you don't believe I'm his crewmate,
so I'm not telling you what I saw, dumbass!

222
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,550
Annoying punk!

223
00:16:12,070 --> 00:16:14,690
Hey, who made this food?

224
00:16:14,690 --> 00:16:18,390
Oh? That is a discerning
palate you have there.

225
00:16:18,390 --> 00:16:24,000
Not only does it taste sublime, it's as if...
my body is getting rejuvenated.

226
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:28,430
Indeed. This is aggression cuisine!

227
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:32,340
Many chefs on this island
can make this dish!

228
00:16:32,340 --> 00:16:34,310
Yes!

229
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:34,310
Yes!

230
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,310
Yes!            Yes!

231
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:34,310
Yes!            Yes!

232
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:35,870
– Yes!
– Yes!

233
00:16:36,570 --> 00:16:40,660
Behold! The candies of this island
have beautiful yet strong physiques!

234
00:16:41,780 --> 00:16:43,110
Kind hearts, too.

235
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:48,690
My candies developed this vayy
by eating aggression cuisine!

236
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:51,820
Your diet decides your condition,

237
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:52,960
your physique,

238
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,030
and your personality!

239
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:56,930
You are vhaat you eat!

240
00:16:56,930 --> 00:17:01,070
If 100 percent of the human population
drank milk every day...

241
00:17:04,930 --> 00:17:07,650
crime across the voorld vould disappear, no?!

242
00:17:07,650 --> 00:17:08,240
Hm?

243
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,210
You see...

244
00:17:09,210 --> 00:17:12,310
no aggression, no progression!

245
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:15,510
Using food to build one's physique...

246
00:17:15,510 --> 00:17:18,480
I never thought about it that way.

247
00:17:18,950 --> 00:17:23,850
So every day I cook for them
could help their development?

248
00:17:27,290 --> 00:17:28,500
And then...

249
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:33,560
I could make Nami and Robin's
bodies even sexier?!

250
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,230
Vhaat should I do viith you?!

251
00:17:35,230 --> 00:17:37,100
What should I do?!

252
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,070
I'm burning with passion!

253
00:17:39,070 --> 00:17:41,770
Please teach me aggression cuisine!

254
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:44,640
The answer is no!

255
00:17:46,330 --> 00:17:47,470
Ouch...

256
00:17:47,470 --> 00:17:50,450
The Kamabakka Queendom's 99 Vital Recipes

257
00:17:50,450 --> 00:17:54,450
have been passed down as part of
the Newkama Kenpo secret arts:

258
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:56,190
Bride Training!

259
00:17:56,190 --> 00:17:58,690
It vill be a cold day in hell...

260
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:01,260
before I let a total stranger
like you learn them!

261
00:18:01,260 --> 00:18:04,420
That is, unless you open
your heart to your femininity!

262
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:07,730
Study Newkama kenpo!

263
00:18:08,370 --> 00:18:10,170
I refuse!

264
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:15,780
I was not born to merely befriend the ladies.

265
00:18:15,780 --> 00:18:17,840
I am a man who was born...

266
00:18:18,110 --> 00:18:20,810
to give them my love!

267
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:24,850
Heehaw!

268
00:18:24,850 --> 00:18:27,070
– Yahoo!
– Yay!

269
00:18:27,070 --> 00:18:28,120
– Sanji!
– Yay!

270
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:31,560
Vhaat a compelling speech! I like you!

271
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:33,420
So I vill give you a chance!

272
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:34,260
A chance?

273
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:41,230
On this island resides ninety-nine
Newkama Kenpo grandmasters,

274
00:18:41,230 --> 00:18:44,740
and I vill hand out one recipe to each of them.

275
00:18:45,210 --> 00:18:50,940
If you are indeed a pirate,
then steal every one of those recipes!

276
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:53,850
However! It vill be hell for you, day and night,

277
00:18:53,850 --> 00:18:58,750
as every Newkama here attempts
to put this Ssveets dress on you!

278
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:02,250
I vaant to see if you maintain
your manly composure!

279
00:19:04,890 --> 00:19:06,950
Sanji-kins!

280
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:08,790
We won't let you sleep!

281
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:09,860
The Sweets dress.

282
00:19:10,660 --> 00:19:14,700
I will make you remember
the joy of wearing a skirt!

283
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:15,730
Sanji!

284
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:17,640
It's nice to be girly!

285
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,470
You...

286
00:19:21,470 --> 00:19:25,580
versus the Newkama Kenpo head temple!

287
00:19:26,380 --> 00:19:29,400
Come out on top,
and I vill even give you a ship!

288
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,770
Vhaatever you vaant is yours!

289
00:19:31,770 --> 00:19:33,520
Now, decide!

290
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:37,490
Hey you, cook!

291
00:19:38,460 --> 00:19:41,060
Join my crew!

292
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:44,500
Be the cook on my pirate ship!

293
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:49,140
Is your lack of an answer
an indication that you give up?

294
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:51,180
Because when you lose–

295
00:19:51,180 --> 00:19:52,740
When I win...

296
00:19:52,740 --> 00:19:53,640
Wha...?

297
00:19:53,930 --> 00:19:56,390
When I beat all of them...

298
00:19:57,110 --> 00:20:00,580
I bet I'll be much stronger than I am now.

299
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:04,980
Even if you pierce his body
with hundreds of weapons,

300
00:20:04,980 --> 00:20:10,290
nobody stands a chance against
a spear of blind determination.

301
00:20:10,490 --> 00:20:12,030
Hey, Luffy...

302
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:15,430
don't lose.

303
00:20:16,870 --> 00:20:19,550
I am hoping to head out someday...

304
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:21,040
to the Grand Line.

305
00:20:21,570 --> 00:20:23,330
Then let's go now!

306
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:25,410
It's not the right time yet.

307
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:28,640
Hey...

308
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,750
have you heard of the All Blue?!

309
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:31,300
Nope.

310
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:33,320
You've seriously never heard of it?!

311
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:35,120
That sea itself is a miracle!

312
00:20:37,650 --> 00:20:40,810
We both have foolish dreams.

313
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:47,380
To achieve my goal—to find the All Blue...

314
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:48,390
Sanji?

315
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:52,810
Yeah. I'll come along on your journey
to become King of the Pirates!

316
00:20:52,810 --> 00:20:53,790
Huh?

317
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,850
I'll be the cook for your ship.

318
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:04,150
Luffy, the next time we meet...

319
00:21:04,410 --> 00:21:05,880
I will...

320
00:21:07,310 --> 00:21:14,060
support you as the world's greatest cook
so that you can become King of the Pirates.

321
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:16,390
I will...

322
00:21:17,990 --> 00:21:19,310
live through...

323
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,480
this hell!

324
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,530
I accept...

325
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,500
your challenge!

326
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:35,010
That is great!

327
00:21:35,010 --> 00:21:37,010
No holding back, dearies!

328
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:38,380
Here I come!

329
00:21:40,460 --> 00:21:42,430
I will definitely...

330
00:21:42,430 --> 00:21:43,820
win!

331
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:52,620
On the small sky island, Weatheria...

332
00:21:53,210 --> 00:21:54,760
The research she stole...

333
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:56,050
...the weather ball...

334
00:21:56,050 --> 00:21:58,200
...and her hostage, Mr. Haredas!

335
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:01,300
We won't forgive you just because
you returned everything!

336
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:03,770
I'm sorry. I truly regret my actions.

337
00:22:03,770 --> 00:22:05,720
No, we can't trust her!

338
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:08,510
Strip her of all that she has and banish her!

339
00:22:08,510 --> 00:22:10,140
Please don't!

340
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:12,080
Well then, to prove my remorse,

341
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:14,710
I will throw myself into the sea.

342
00:22:14,710 --> 00:22:15,370
– What?!
– What?!

343
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:17,660
Please forgive me in my next life!

344
00:22:17,660 --> 00:22:18,280
– What?!
– What?!

345
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,320
Farewell!

346
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,920
We made her cry!

347
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:23,540
Don't jump the gun!

348
00:22:23,540 --> 00:22:27,120
You're too young to just up
and throw your life away!

349
00:22:27,630 --> 00:22:28,630
Goodbye...

350
00:22:28,630 --> 00:22:30,290
– We're sorry!
– We're sorry!

351
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:33,900
Sounds good. I forgive you.

352
00:22:35,510 --> 00:22:39,910
Well, I'll be staying here awhile
to study up on your weather science.

353
00:22:39,910 --> 00:22:42,300
Oh, my name is Nami.
Miss Nami if you please.

354
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:46,440
Also, I'll need a house of my own.
Privacy is important, you know.

355
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:51,080
I require a soft, fluffy bed,
a hot tub, and a walk-in closet.

356
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:53,960
I'm counting on you, sky geezers.

357
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,590
So, let's do our best!

358
00:22:55,590 --> 00:22:56,260
Yeah!

359
00:22:57,450 --> 00:23:00,150
Mr. Haredas, say something already!

360
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:02,030
Good grief...

361
00:23:04,870 --> 00:23:10,810
Weatheria drifts around the world
wherever the wind may take it.

362
00:23:10,810 --> 00:23:14,230
We sometimes visit the surface
to gather goods and information,

363
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:17,100
and then we continue on our way.

364
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:17,980
Information?

365
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:21,010
Well, records mostly.

366
00:23:21,010 --> 00:23:26,350
Records regarding the Grand Line's
unbelievable weather phenomena,

367
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:28,620
many of which are still–

368
00:23:27,660 --> 00:23:28,620
What's this?!

369
00:23:28,620 --> 00:23:29,960
Are you listening?

370
00:23:30,260 --> 00:23:32,060
Huh?! You've gotta be kidding me!

371
00:23:32,660 --> 00:23:34,260
Lightning strikes like rain?!

372
00:23:34,260 --> 00:23:38,030
Indeed. It literally rains lightning.

373
00:23:38,030 --> 00:23:40,900
The lightning strikes the island like it's raining.

374
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:43,870
It happens on an island in the New World.

375
00:23:43,870 --> 00:23:46,470
If you plan to cross that sea,

376
00:23:46,470 --> 00:23:50,170
remember that it defies
common sense like no sea before it.

377
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:54,450
Please... teach me, Mr. Haredas.

378
00:23:54,790 --> 00:23:56,410
The New World's weather...

379
00:23:58,580 --> 00:24:00,220
Teach me all about it!

380
00:24:01,220 --> 00:24:02,990
You seem desperate.

381
00:24:02,990 --> 00:24:07,360
Well, of course I am! My actions
determine the lives of my crewmates!

382
00:24:07,360 --> 00:24:09,260
I'm their navigator!

383
00:24:09,260 --> 00:24:12,400
Out at sea, I have the
biggest responsibility of all!

384
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:17,330
It's my job to take the captain
wherever it is he wishes to go!

385
00:24:22,810 --> 00:24:26,840
Luffy says he wants to
become King of the Pirates,

386
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:30,710
so I can't take my job as a navigator lightly!

387
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:36,740
It must make your captain very happy
to have such a thoughtful crew member.

388
00:24:37,950 --> 00:24:39,300
I don't have a choice.

389
00:24:39,300 --> 00:24:40,520
You don't?

390
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:46,560
That's right. I mean, he talks a big game,
but he's utterly clueless about the ocean.

391
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:59,550
He's always doing the craziest things.

392
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:00,640
If I left him alone...

393
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:04,280
Luffy...

394
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,820
Help me...

395
00:25:14,190 --> 00:25:16,830
Of course I will!

396
00:25:21,180 --> 00:25:24,300
He'd get himself killed without me.

397
00:25:26,730 --> 00:25:29,310
He's a high-maintenance idiot!

398
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:34,080
He sounds like one troublesome captain!

399
00:25:34,850 --> 00:25:38,420
He is. That's why I'm gonna help him.

400
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:41,850
This time, I will!

401
00:25:41,850 --> 00:25:44,670
Hey, tell me about the weather balls.

402
00:25:44,670 --> 00:25:49,240
You ask like it's no big deal! This is
Weatheria's greatest invention, after all!

403
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:53,560
In the wrong hands, they could
throw the entire world into disarray!

404
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:55,600
So it has combat potential?

405
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:58,750
Hey now, don't go saying
such dangerous things!

406
00:25:58,750 --> 00:25:59,770
Stop grinning!

407
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:14,710
Nami!

408
00:26:15,220 --> 00:26:18,190
You're one of us!

409
00:26:42,660 --> 00:26:47,520
This is the Kingdom of Armsolong
on Sword Mountain Island in the Grand Line.

410
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:50,300
Come one! Come all!

411
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:57,490
This creature has the
appearance of a real skeleton!

412
00:26:57,490 --> 00:27:00,330
What's more, his arms only have a single joint!

413
00:27:00,330 --> 00:27:04,500
Have you ever seen
a rarer creature than this?!

414
00:27:04,500 --> 00:27:07,840
Hey! Don't pull a fast one, you con artists!

415
00:27:08,830 --> 00:27:11,020
What? Does he not fascinate you?

416
00:27:11,020 --> 00:27:14,680
That thing hasn't moved one bit!

417
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:17,010
It's just a big doll, isn't it?!

418
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:22,840
Luffy has made his decision.

419
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:25,450
And so, I should make one too.

420
00:27:25,450 --> 00:27:28,560
Hey, skeleton! Don't jerk us around!

421
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:30,960
I cannot just sit here!

422
00:27:31,660 --> 00:27:35,100
Oh, so you understand? That's right, move!

423
00:27:35,100 --> 00:27:37,070
This is a show, after all!

424
00:27:37,070 --> 00:27:39,860
What can I do to help?

425
00:27:39,860 --> 00:27:44,540
Just moving around would be
plenty helpful! So move already!

426
00:27:44,980 --> 00:27:46,110
What's going on here?!

427
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:58,060
When you saw me for the first time,

428
00:27:58,060 --> 00:28:03,440
you weren't the least bit scared,
and you even asked me to join your crew.

429
00:28:04,330 --> 00:28:06,500
Anyway... Hey, you!

430
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:08,970
Join my crew!

431
00:28:09,430 --> 00:28:11,100
Yes. That sounds lovely.

432
00:28:11,100 --> 00:28:13,750
– What?!
– What?!

433
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,010
Fifty long years...

434
00:28:17,210 --> 00:28:22,600
Could you imagine my joy, especially
after drifting on that dark sea for so long?

435
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:28,990
A certain man stole my shadow.

436
00:28:29,390 --> 00:28:31,620
Don't act like we're strangers!

437
00:28:31,620 --> 00:28:34,390
If you need your shadow,
I'll get it back for you!

438
00:28:34,390 --> 00:28:38,800
Do you realize how brilliantly
you were shining to me?

439
00:28:39,730 --> 00:28:45,670
Fifty years of hoping for a miracle,
and that moment fulfilled my wish.

440
00:28:45,670 --> 00:28:47,010
Give me back my money!

441
00:28:47,010 --> 00:28:48,140
Yeah!

442
00:28:48,140 --> 00:28:53,140
Damn! I thought he'd be our
meal ticket, but it looks hopeless.

443
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:55,450
If he won't comply, we'll just have to–

444
00:28:55,450 --> 00:28:56,510
What the...?!

445
00:28:56,510 --> 00:28:57,690
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

446
00:28:57,690 --> 00:28:59,090
– Oh...?
– Huh...?

447
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:00,980
Forty degrees!

448
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:05,060
– What?!
– What?!

449
00:29:05,060 --> 00:29:07,320
Ah! That's difficult!

450
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:09,920
He's really talking and moving!

451
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:11,130
How creepy!

452
00:29:11,130 --> 00:29:12,730
What is that thing?!

453
00:29:12,730 --> 00:29:17,730
If I try going below 45 degrees,
I end up slipping.

454
00:29:17,730 --> 00:29:20,640
However, once I can master this...

455
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:25,720
I may be of more use to Luffy.

456
00:29:26,780 --> 00:29:29,610
Or perhaps I should find another way...

457
00:29:35,090 --> 00:29:36,520
He's got a guitar!

458
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:37,750
What's he about to do?

459
00:29:37,750 --> 00:29:39,900
What is it this time?!

460
00:29:39,900 --> 00:29:43,590
Anything extra is too much!
This is just a freak show!

461
00:29:43,590 --> 00:29:47,850
"Freak show" works for me!
Call it whatever you wish.

462
00:29:47,850 --> 00:29:52,040
"Loneliness" no longer exists in my vocabulary!

463
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:56,540
Ladies and gentlemen!

464
00:29:56,540 --> 00:29:58,690
I'm sure you're all bored just staring at me.

465
00:29:58,690 --> 00:30:00,580
What's this rhythm?

466
00:30:00,580 --> 00:30:02,320
It speaks to my soul!

467
00:30:03,950 --> 00:30:07,180
Please listen to my new single,

468
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:09,750
"Bone to Be Wild"!

469
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:21,160
Meanwhile, just below
the East Blue's colossal bridge...

470
00:30:22,140 --> 00:30:25,020
Why the sudden change of heart?

471
00:30:25,020 --> 00:30:27,340
You're coming with us to Baltigo?

472
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:30,050
If so, we are extremely grateful.

473
00:30:30,050 --> 00:30:33,860
Dragon has always wanted to meet you.

474
00:30:34,350 --> 00:30:37,020
I didn't know you were such charitable people.

475
00:30:37,020 --> 00:30:39,810
I wish you would have
sought me out much sooner.

476
00:30:39,810 --> 00:30:45,380
W-We're sorry! We hadn't heard
about your team-up with Crocodile.

477
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:49,820
I'm joking. Just a bit of fun, but I apologize.

478
00:30:49,820 --> 00:30:53,030
I'm glad things turned out the way they did.

479
00:30:53,930 --> 00:30:58,350
Set sail! Set sail for Baltigo!

480
00:31:12,110 --> 00:31:14,060
Seventy-nine million belly?!

481
00:31:14,060 --> 00:31:16,990
A bounty that high for an eight-year-old girl?!

482
00:31:16,990 --> 00:31:22,200
They say she's a survivor of those Ohara devils
who were plotting the world's destruction.

483
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:24,040
Ohara?

484
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:28,940
I don't know how, but they say
that she sank six Marine battleships.

485
00:31:28,940 --> 00:31:30,830
That explains the high bounty.

486
00:31:32,740 --> 00:31:36,740
She's a devil's spawn
who shouldn't be left alive!

487
00:31:39,170 --> 00:31:41,360
Alright! Just wait right there!

488
00:31:42,470 --> 00:31:44,510
Why are you trying to save me?!

489
00:31:44,510 --> 00:31:48,440
When did I ever ask you to do this?!

490
00:31:53,910 --> 00:31:57,190
I just... want to die!

491
00:32:03,830 --> 00:32:04,830
No way!

492
00:32:04,830 --> 00:32:06,540
Are you all insane?!

493
00:32:06,540 --> 00:32:10,140
You're all as good as dead after
making the world your enemy!

494
00:32:10,140 --> 00:32:15,250
Bring it on!

495
00:32:20,950 --> 00:32:23,260
Robin, please come inside.

496
00:32:23,260 --> 00:32:25,030
It's cold out here.

497
00:32:25,460 --> 00:32:26,970
I'll be fine out here.

498
00:32:26,970 --> 00:32:30,590
I'm a pirate. You are revolutionaries.

499
00:32:30,590 --> 00:32:32,750
I can't trust you so easily.

500
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:37,170
I won't enter a cabin
where there's no escape route.

501
00:32:37,170 --> 00:32:41,000
But that's...! We have
no intention of harming you!

502
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:45,700
Just let me stay. Back when I was
on my own, this was how I lived.

503
00:32:46,630 --> 00:32:48,650
My apologies! Very well.

504
00:32:48,650 --> 00:32:51,350
Hey! Bring out as many
warm blankets as you can!

505
00:32:51,350 --> 00:32:54,100
And something hot to drink and eat, too!

506
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:56,410
B-But we set that all up inside...

507
00:32:56,410 --> 00:32:59,350
Hop to it! A wind screen and sofa too!

508
00:32:59,350 --> 00:32:59,920
Yes, sir!

509
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:08,490
Luffy, if I go to your father and let the
world's tides carry me where they will,

510
00:33:08,490 --> 00:33:11,670
I wonder if I can become a little stronger?

511
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:16,660
Wanting to become stronger
for the sake of someone else...

512
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:19,750
I'd never considered it before.

513
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:27,850
We now return to Mech Island
on the Grand Line...

514
00:33:27,850 --> 00:33:31,020
Futureland, Baldimore...

515
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:35,560
We've investigated the destruction
of Doctor Vegapunk's laboratory...

516
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:39,060
but we still haven't found the culprit.

517
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:40,830
Hey! Hurry up!

518
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:48,410
It wouldn't be an exaggeration to call
this the greatest loss of the century.

519
00:33:48,690 --> 00:33:50,800
Do you know anything about it?

520
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:54,940
I heard that an intruder
resembling a gorilla entered the lab.

521
00:33:54,940 --> 00:33:57,510
This is a real head-scratcher.

522
00:33:57,510 --> 00:34:03,520
It's impossible to reach this island
without an icebreaker ship.

523
00:34:03,910 --> 00:34:06,290
But no one seems to have seen it.

524
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:11,590
They say that the intruder was
Cyborg Franky of the Straw Hat Pirates,

525
00:34:12,100 --> 00:34:17,170
but he was spotted less than
a month ago on Sabaody Archipelago.

526
00:34:17,170 --> 00:34:20,360
We have no idea what route or means
he used to get to Baldimore.

527
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:24,000
Captain Gorilla! The search party is
departing for the snow mountains!

528
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:26,340
Very well! I shall accompany them!

529
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:28,130
Th-This is...!

530
00:34:28,130 --> 00:34:31,610
The explosion exposed a hidden entrance.

531
00:34:31,610 --> 00:34:35,020
I can hardly believe it. We had no idea...

532
00:34:36,590 --> 00:34:42,330
that there was a second laboratory in here.

533
00:34:42,890 --> 00:34:47,780
This seems to be where he created
all those cyborg animal guards.

534
00:34:49,650 --> 00:34:50,970
Hey, don't break anything!

535
00:34:50,970 --> 00:34:53,170
You're one to talk, old guy!

536
00:34:53,500 --> 00:35:00,740
The blown-up lab had some radical inventions
that would have changed how people live,

537
00:35:00,740 --> 00:35:07,500
but I was more interested
in the weaponry I found here.

538
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:11,620
This is amazing!

539
00:35:11,620 --> 00:35:14,990
It's everything from warships
to human genetics!

540
00:35:14,990 --> 00:35:17,960
What's going on inside this guy's head?

541
00:35:20,100 --> 00:35:22,710
Okay, I've made up my mind!

542
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:24,700
I'm gonna live here!

543
00:35:24,700 --> 00:35:25,670
Wha...?! Live here?!

544
00:35:25,670 --> 00:35:26,540
Yeah!

545
00:35:28,950 --> 00:35:31,740
I'll come down the mountain
sometimes for more cola,

546
00:35:31,740 --> 00:35:34,800
so don't forget to keep
your house stocked, you hear?!

547
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:37,450
Don't sweat it!

548
00:35:37,450 --> 00:35:43,520
As long as you don't rat me out,
I'll live here and keep to myself.

549
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:46,520
Quit screamin'! It's just my face!

550
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,930
Don't look at us!

551
00:35:47,930 --> 00:35:49,160
Your face is too scary!

552
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:52,160
How's this? A tiger-skin rug.

553
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:54,580
– Much better.
– Much better.

554
00:35:54,580 --> 00:35:56,530
Frah... Frah... Frah-nky!

555
00:35:57,740 --> 00:35:59,850
I'm freezing. Especially my legs.

556
00:35:59,850 --> 00:36:01,200
Why won't you put on pants?

557
00:36:09,930 --> 00:36:15,890
Would you please sail
on the ship that I've built?

558
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:23,030
Luffy... you helped me carry out my dream.

559
00:36:24,890 --> 00:36:26,380
Franky!

560
00:36:27,330 --> 00:36:30,040
Thanks for the ship!

561
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:33,470
It really is the best! We'll take good care of it!

562
00:36:33,890 --> 00:36:36,840
If you want your bikini back,

563
00:36:37,110 --> 00:36:39,280
you'll just have to join our crew!

564
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:46,780
You took me along for the ride
in this wild, wide world.

565
00:36:48,180 --> 00:36:54,760
Passing through sea after sea,
overcoming countless battles and troubles.

566
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:58,460
And once we've sailed to the end of the sea,

567
00:36:58,460 --> 00:37:02,350
then we can truly say
she was the ship of dreams.

568
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:06,140
Hey, Luffy.

569
00:37:07,170 --> 00:37:10,240
The Sunny still hasn't shown her full potential!

570
00:37:11,580 --> 00:37:14,510
And the captain to make
the Sunny my dream ship...?

571
00:37:15,490 --> 00:37:16,800
That's you.

572
00:37:18,850 --> 00:37:24,450
I'll learn the technologies necessary to get
the better of tough adventures to come...

573
00:37:24,450 --> 00:37:27,020
tougher than any so far.

574
00:37:27,020 --> 00:37:28,690
So, Luffy...!

575
00:37:30,650 --> 00:37:32,360
Hey. The tiger's on fire.

576
00:37:37,340 --> 00:37:39,270
Ow, ow, ow, ow...!

577
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:41,540
What's that?!

578
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:44,410
A monster?! Be careful!

579
00:37:57,100 --> 00:38:02,890
So, Luffy, let's overcome the rough
waves of the New World together!

580
00:38:06,470 --> 00:38:09,690
This incident in the Grand Line
is forever referred to as:

581
00:38:09,690 --> 00:38:13,930
"The Legend of the Burning Spirit Beast of Baldimore."

582
00:38:16,500 --> 00:38:17,560
Meanwhile...

583
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:21,080
on the Bowin Archipelago in the Grand Line...

584
00:38:24,300 --> 00:38:26,970
What is it now'n, Usopp'n?

585
00:38:26,970 --> 00:38:29,890
Gotta burn this fat! Gotta get in shape!

586
00:38:29,890 --> 00:38:32,230
Oh! That's a great idea'n!

587
00:38:32,230 --> 00:38:33,760
Then I'll be stronger!

588
00:38:34,230 --> 00:38:37,310
Good! You can't get off the island otherwise'n!

589
00:38:37,310 --> 00:38:39,910
And then... I'll be even stronger!

590
00:38:39,910 --> 00:38:41,780
Yes! That sounds good too'n!

591
00:38:41,780 --> 00:38:44,610
And then I'll be much, much stronger!

592
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:46,600
Oh? Th-That much'n?!

593
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:49,980
Much, much, much, much,
much, much stronger!

594
00:38:49,980 --> 00:38:51,970
Wow! You're very motivated'n!

595
00:38:53,450 --> 00:38:55,780
To get you up and working
out so vigorously'n...

596
00:38:56,930 --> 00:38:59,880
What exactly was written in that paper'n?

597
00:39:05,020 --> 00:39:08,360
I received a message from our captain.

598
00:39:08,860 --> 00:39:09,830
A message?

599
00:39:10,600 --> 00:39:13,660
What're you talking about? Get on already.

600
00:39:16,470 --> 00:39:19,060
You're one of us now, aren't you?

601
00:39:29,550 --> 00:39:32,260
Luffy!

602
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:36,160
U-Usopp?

603
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:38,650
Y-You...

604
00:39:38,650 --> 00:39:40,500
were here too?

605
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:45,430
Defeat him! We're all
going back together, Luffy!

606
00:39:45,430 --> 00:39:47,460
Of course we will!

607
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,220
I thought...

608
00:39:52,220 --> 00:39:59,380
that Luffy could become King of the Pirates
all on his own while I stood by and watched.

609
00:40:00,810 --> 00:40:03,080
We've finally made it this far!

610
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:09,500
We'll see this wall again when we
cross the other half of the world!

611
00:40:09,500 --> 00:40:10,530
When that happens,

612
00:40:10,820 --> 00:40:13,070
I'll be King of the Pirates!

613
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:16,200
But I was wrong.

614
00:40:16,200 --> 00:40:19,260
He has lots of enemies stronger than him.

615
00:40:19,830 --> 00:40:22,000
Even Luffy can lose!

616
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:25,600
He's pushing himself too hard!
He's crying out in agony!

617
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:26,840
That's why...

618
00:40:27,100 --> 00:40:30,470
he needs to depend on my strength!

619
00:40:35,010 --> 00:40:36,720
Heracles'n!

620
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:38,630
I wanna get stronger!

621
00:40:38,630 --> 00:40:42,120
I wanna get much, much,
much stronger, and...!

622
00:40:44,450 --> 00:40:47,260
Please... Master Heracles'n...

623
00:40:47,670 --> 00:40:49,900
Huh? M-Master'n...?

624
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:53,610
I've been curious about
those weapons of yours.

625
00:40:53,610 --> 00:40:58,940
Your strength is what allows you to survive
on this island. Teach me your ways!

626
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:01,940
Strength'n? I'm a strong master'n?

627
00:41:01,940 --> 00:41:04,810
Yeah! My master is amazingly strong!

628
00:41:04,810 --> 00:41:06,980
And, my name is...

629
00:41:08,140 --> 00:41:09,450
Heracles'n!

630
00:41:09,450 --> 00:41:11,590
That's such a cool name!

631
00:41:12,300 --> 00:41:15,630
R-Right! Take a seat, Usopp'n.

632
00:41:15,630 --> 00:41:17,280
Yes, Master!

633
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:19,930
Listen up, Usopp, my student'n!

634
00:41:20,700 --> 00:41:23,830
Much of the local flora consists of pop green.

635
00:41:23,830 --> 00:41:28,520
They can sprout anywhere in an instant
and have quite the mean streak!

636
00:41:29,730 --> 00:41:32,030
Behold! Their seeds'n.

637
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,970
Pop green?

638
00:41:34,970 --> 00:41:36,440
Indeed'n!

639
00:41:37,470 --> 00:41:39,620
They all have their uses'n.

640
00:41:39,620 --> 00:41:41,210
Is that so'n?

641
00:41:41,210 --> 00:41:43,450
Wait for me, Luffy!

642
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:49,960
Run, Usopp'n! This forest
will make you stronger'n!

643
00:41:50,820 --> 00:41:53,230
To help you become King of the Pirates,

644
00:41:53,230 --> 00:41:57,010
I will become a true King of Snipers!

645
00:42:03,700 --> 00:42:10,050
Now to Gloom Island on the Grand Line,
in the ruins of the Muggy Kingdom...

646
00:42:10,960 --> 00:42:11,940
Please!

647
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:21,980
Teach me the way of your sword!

648
00:42:22,700 --> 00:42:25,110
I'm disappointed in you, Roronoa.

649
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:30,130
You would beg your enemy to instruct you?

650
00:42:30,710 --> 00:42:31,900
How shameless!

651
00:42:33,860 --> 00:42:37,070
Leave. I have no business
with a wretch like you.

652
00:42:37,070 --> 00:42:40,880
It would seem I overestimated you.

653
00:42:43,510 --> 00:42:46,680
What's your game?
You're embarrassing yourself.

654
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:49,600
I want to become stronger!

655
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:52,860
Powerless against baboons
and incapable of setting sail,

656
00:42:52,860 --> 00:42:57,790
you returned here, tail between your legs;
I have nothing to teach a man such as you.

657
00:42:57,790 --> 00:42:59,420
I defeated the baboons.

658
00:43:00,820 --> 00:43:02,190
Did he now?

659
00:43:03,480 --> 00:43:06,160
All that's left is to take your head!

660
00:43:06,160 --> 00:43:12,570
But I'm not so stupid to think
I can beat you right now.

661
00:43:12,570 --> 00:43:20,580
Baffling... If you still see me as an enemy,
why bow down and demand tutelage?

662
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:22,670
For what purpose?!

663
00:43:24,390 --> 00:43:26,460
To surpass you!

664
00:43:34,300 --> 00:43:39,100
You would have me temper the very sword
whose blade would claim my head?

665
00:43:39,100 --> 00:43:42,920
You are a strange one. What foolishness...

666
00:43:42,920 --> 00:43:46,070
And still, you remain shameless.

667
00:43:46,070 --> 00:43:50,610
It would seem... your ambition
exceeds even your pride.

668
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:56,180
You there, ghost girl... Tend to his wounds.

669
00:43:57,040 --> 00:43:59,520
Hey! Don't tell me what to do!

670
00:44:00,420 --> 00:44:02,530
Training commences upon your recovery.

671
00:44:03,500 --> 00:44:07,810
Dammit! Every last one of you
is so demanding of me!

672
00:44:07,810 --> 00:44:10,200
Come on, get back to your room!

673
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:13,930
What a clumsy fool.

674
00:44:14,620 --> 00:44:20,930
When a man of his caliber sets aside his pride,
it is always for the sake of another.

675
00:44:22,060 --> 00:44:25,570
It's "3D" crossed out with "2Y" written next?

676
00:44:25,570 --> 00:44:28,740
You're right! It's tattooed
onto Straw Hat's right arm!

677
00:44:28,740 --> 00:44:33,900
We made a promise to meet
at a certain place in three days.

678
00:44:34,860 --> 00:44:36,850
So much for that plan.

679
00:44:37,150 --> 00:44:40,880
So "3D" stands for "three days"?

680
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:44,560
But since the "3D" is
crossed out, the "2Y" means...

681
00:44:45,140 --> 00:44:46,000
Two years.

682
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:47,260
Two years?!

683
00:44:47,260 --> 00:44:51,350
We won't be meeting up in
three days, but in two years.

684
00:44:51,350 --> 00:44:55,700
Everything else was to distract
from his true intentions.

685
00:44:55,700 --> 00:45:02,050
This message was meant only for us.
Luffy has made his decision.

686
00:45:02,700 --> 00:45:06,770
As we are, we'd be rushing headlong
into disaster in the New World.

687
00:45:06,770 --> 00:45:09,050
We'll stay put, grow stronger...

688
00:45:10,150 --> 00:45:13,220
and then we'll definitely set sail once more!

689
00:45:13,690 --> 00:45:17,150
– See you at Sabaody Archipelago in two years!
– See you at Sabaody Archipelago in two years!

690
00:45:27,900 --> 00:45:29,370
Here he comes.

691
00:45:34,140 --> 00:45:36,850
Jinbe! Thanks for everything!

692
00:45:36,850 --> 00:45:40,580
I'm the one who ought to be thanking you!

693
00:45:46,720 --> 00:45:51,660
You listened to my plea and
helped me escape from Impel Down,

694
00:45:51,660 --> 00:45:55,630
and though I am shamed, I go on living.

695
00:45:55,630 --> 00:45:57,730
My sincerest apologies!

696
00:45:59,030 --> 00:46:02,200
I thought I told you to stop that.

697
00:46:02,200 --> 00:46:08,310
If not for you, I probably wouldn't
have gotten to Marine Headquarters.

698
00:46:08,780 --> 00:46:10,270
Raise your head.

699
00:46:21,600 --> 00:46:23,590
I suppose so.

700
00:46:23,590 --> 00:46:28,330
And I might have the chance
to help you again someday.

701
00:46:29,340 --> 00:46:32,970
With that said, let us meet again
in two years at Fishman Island!

702
00:46:32,970 --> 00:46:37,770
I look forward to the day when you
arrive together with your crew!

703
00:46:37,770 --> 00:46:38,850
Sure!

704
00:46:41,780 --> 00:46:43,550
– Take care!
– Farewell!

705
00:46:53,320 --> 00:46:55,490
This island will do the trick.

706
00:46:55,490 --> 00:47:00,330
Known as the Island of Forty-Eight Seasons,
its climate ruthlessly shifts once per week.

707
00:47:00,330 --> 00:47:02,200
Luffy!

708
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:09,000
I will bring you food from the
Isle of Women each and every day!

709
00:47:09,000 --> 00:47:11,640
What?! Seriously, Hancock?

710
00:47:11,640 --> 00:47:15,160
Then bring more of that special dish,
the gorgon something-or-other!

711
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:17,210
It was so good!

712
00:47:17,210 --> 00:47:19,050
O-Of course!

713
00:47:19,050 --> 00:47:21,750
– Wow! Snake Princess!
– Wow! Snake Princess!

714
00:47:21,750 --> 00:47:25,490
Whatever your heart desires most,
I will bring it to you!

715
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:30,690
Also... that's officially the tenth time
you have used my name.

716
00:47:32,540 --> 00:47:35,500
Th-Then... we must be engaged!

717
00:47:35,500 --> 00:47:39,700
Nyo you are nyot! And why
do you keep moving backward?!

718
00:47:39,700 --> 00:47:43,910
Hancock, we can't have you
pampering him like that.

719
00:47:43,910 --> 00:47:48,300
While Luffy is training, all your women
will have to remain off the island.

720
00:47:48,300 --> 00:47:49,180
What?!

721
00:47:50,380 --> 00:47:55,080
What gives you the right
to decide such things, Rayleigh?!

722
00:47:55,080 --> 00:47:58,450
Your answer will determine
whether you turn to stone!

723
00:47:58,450 --> 00:48:03,930
He can find all the food he needs
in the mountains, forests, rivers, or ocean!

724
00:48:03,930 --> 00:48:06,780
Please release his nyose, Snake Princess!

725
00:48:06,780 --> 00:48:11,370
If he can't handle basic survival skills,
he'll never make it as a pirate!

726
00:48:11,370 --> 00:48:13,340
This is all to help Luffy!

727
00:48:15,340 --> 00:48:18,450
Did you say... this is to help Luffy?

728
00:48:19,350 --> 00:48:20,510
I did.

729
00:48:20,510 --> 00:48:22,440
If it is to help Luffy...

730
00:48:24,960 --> 00:48:26,380
then I shall endure it!

731
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:31,620
But Rayleigh, this island
is extremely dangerous.

732
00:48:31,620 --> 00:48:33,190
If anything happens to him–

733
00:48:33,190 --> 00:48:36,000
If nothing happens to him,
it wouldn't be training.

734
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:38,100
Send prayers if you're worried.

735
00:48:40,430 --> 00:48:46,070
All right. Now we are the only
two humans on this island.

736
00:48:46,830 --> 00:48:48,770
Take a look at this vast wilderness.

737
00:48:48,770 --> 00:48:55,410
There was once a great civilization here,
but humans eventually lost the battle for survival.

738
00:48:55,410 --> 00:48:58,550
It's a harsh environment,
where only the strong can thrive.

739
00:49:08,930 --> 00:49:10,730
I smell adventure!

740
00:49:16,770 --> 00:49:19,970
The island is crawling with beasts.

741
00:49:20,380 --> 00:49:22,400
There's no counting them all.

742
00:49:23,210 --> 00:49:28,180
In your current state, I sense about
500 that you can't beat.

743
00:49:28,860 --> 00:49:32,380
You'll need to become stronger
to even sleep at night.

744
00:49:32,380 --> 00:49:36,250
How can you tell what's here
or how many there are?

745
00:49:36,250 --> 00:49:40,520
It's not just me. You, too,
will learn to use this power.

746
00:49:41,380 --> 00:49:43,230
The power known as haki!

747
00:49:49,030 --> 00:49:51,930
Hey, look out! Something's coming, Rayleigh!

748
00:49:51,930 --> 00:49:54,380
Gramps! Behind you! Behind you!

749
00:49:54,380 --> 00:50:00,440
Listen well, Luffy. Haki is a latent
power dwelling within everyone.

750
00:50:00,440 --> 00:50:03,230
An elephant?! It's five times
as big as a normal one!

751
00:50:03,230 --> 00:50:04,880
That elephant is so cool!

752
00:50:05,800 --> 00:50:09,250
Presence. Fighting spirit. Control.

753
00:50:09,250 --> 00:50:13,880
People use it in much the same way
as their normal senses.

754
00:50:15,330 --> 00:50:18,920
However, most humans don't
even realize they have this power,

755
00:50:18,920 --> 00:50:22,540
or they spend their entire lives
trying in vain to develop it.

756
00:50:25,400 --> 00:50:29,570
To never doubt! That is the strength you seek.

757
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:32,740
L-Look out!

758
00:50:35,250 --> 00:50:36,980
Gear Second!

759
00:50:36,980 --> 00:50:39,080
Jet Pistol!

760
00:50:46,820 --> 00:50:51,930
Damn... What's with this elephant?
He's strong and fast!

761
00:50:55,560 --> 00:50:57,470
Watch closely.

762
00:50:57,470 --> 00:51:00,140
Most haki manifests within two categories.

763
00:51:01,860 --> 00:51:03,100
Look out!

764
00:51:03,100 --> 00:51:04,170
Relax.

765
00:51:04,170 --> 00:51:08,140
The elephant will swing its trunk
at me from the right.

766
00:51:13,520 --> 00:51:16,600
The power to sense your
opponent's presence...

767
00:51:16,600 --> 00:51:19,150
This is observation haki.

768
00:51:23,340 --> 00:51:24,290
Amazing...

769
00:51:24,290 --> 00:51:29,570
Hone this ability to discern the location
and number of foes beyond your vision.

770
00:51:29,570 --> 00:51:34,020
It will even let you predict
your enemy's next move.

771
00:51:34,740 --> 00:51:36,210
A kick with your left foot.

772
00:51:37,140 --> 00:51:38,310
Mantra.

773
00:51:42,950 --> 00:51:46,850
On the sky island of Skypiea,
they call this power "mantra."

774
00:51:49,450 --> 00:51:50,970
That was close!

775
00:51:51,600 --> 00:51:53,960
Next up: armament haki.

776
00:51:53,960 --> 00:51:57,530
Using this power is like wearing invisible armor.

777
00:52:00,960 --> 00:52:01,860
Gramps!

778
00:52:13,050 --> 00:52:16,040
I... I know that one!

779
00:52:16,040 --> 00:52:17,650
Ashigara Dokkoi!

780
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:25,850
Of course, the stronger your armor,
the more powerful your attacks.

781
00:52:28,590 --> 00:52:32,290
Hey, ow! I'm made of rubber, 
but that flick really hurt!

782
00:52:32,290 --> 00:52:36,000
This is the most useful part of this power.

783
00:52:36,700 --> 00:52:43,120
When battling devil fruit users, armament haki
is the most effective way to oppose them.

784
00:52:43,120 --> 00:52:46,520
Otherwise, you must find a weakness
in their individual powers.

785
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:55,140
Even the practically invincible logia types,
who boast freely flowing bodies,

786
00:52:55,140 --> 00:52:57,990
are vulnerable when struck by it.

787
00:52:58,650 --> 00:53:01,620
Was this why you could touch Kizaru?

788
00:53:01,620 --> 00:53:06,930
So, if I used this, even I could fight
Marine guys like Smokey or Aokiji?

789
00:53:11,300 --> 00:53:14,950
People can also imbue
their weapons with this power.

790
00:53:14,950 --> 00:53:17,140
You saw the Kuja Tribe's archery?

791
00:53:17,140 --> 00:53:18,470
Yeah...

792
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:24,080
Then they weren't just steel arrows...!

793
00:53:24,080 --> 00:53:27,450
Observation and armament...

794
00:53:27,450 --> 00:53:29,650
these are two types of haki.

795
00:53:30,030 --> 00:53:31,010
However,

796
00:53:31,010 --> 00:53:35,620
a select few people in the world
can utilize another kind of haki.

797
00:53:40,480 --> 00:53:41,560
Pay attention.

798
00:54:05,930 --> 00:54:08,460
This power controls your opponent!

799
00:54:08,960 --> 00:54:10,840
Conqueror's haki.

800
00:54:12,900 --> 00:54:16,370
Those who have made a name
for themselves in this world,

801
00:54:16,370 --> 00:54:20,360
are often found to possess this power.

802
00:54:20,360 --> 00:54:21,340
However,

803
00:54:21,340 --> 00:54:23,540
while a person can come to control it,

804
00:54:23,540 --> 00:54:27,040
conqueror's haki cannot be
harnessed through training.

805
00:54:27,750 --> 00:54:30,200
It is the very spirit of the user.

806
00:54:31,130 --> 00:54:33,780
It strengthens with individual growth.

807
00:54:34,750 --> 00:54:38,250
That's what you used
back at the auction house!

808
00:54:39,860 --> 00:54:42,080
I'm sure you've experienced it already.

809
00:54:42,620 --> 00:54:46,600
Your potential as a conqueror
is already awakening.

810
00:54:46,600 --> 00:54:51,940
But you should refrain from using it until
you've got it completely under control.

811
00:54:51,940 --> 00:54:56,460
There's a potential for affecting
innocent bystanders around you.

812
00:54:58,810 --> 00:55:00,980
Hm? What is it?

813
00:55:04,680 --> 00:55:06,680
Amazing!

814
00:55:06,680 --> 00:55:12,120
The Pirate King's crew can beat giant monsters
like these without even touching them?

815
00:55:14,520 --> 00:55:16,290
Did your respect for me grow?

816
00:55:17,730 --> 00:55:18,740
Yeah!

817
00:55:19,200 --> 00:55:24,080
But I've seen this haki stuff lots before.

818
00:55:24,720 --> 00:55:27,560
Shanks... Grandpa...

819
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:29,030
Enel and Aisa,

820
00:55:29,030 --> 00:55:32,370
and then there's Hancock
and the Kuja warriors.

821
00:55:32,370 --> 00:55:37,850
I'm sure you have. However, learning
to use haki is not so simple a task.

822
00:55:38,820 --> 00:55:40,100
Right.

823
00:55:46,960 --> 00:55:50,160
Usually, the amount of time
we have wouldn't be enough,

824
00:55:50,160 --> 00:55:51,890
but you have a lot of potential.

825
00:55:52,750 --> 00:56:00,500
In two years, I will teach you the basics of
observation, armament and even conqueror's haki.

826
00:56:00,500 --> 00:56:02,400
Uh-huh.

827
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:07,180
You see, most people tend to specialize
in just one type over the others,

828
00:56:07,180 --> 00:56:09,810
due to their skills or weaknesses.

829
00:56:09,810 --> 00:56:14,350
They gravitate toward the one
they're best at and hone nothing else.

830
00:56:14,350 --> 00:56:18,490
If you become skilled in all three,
you'll achieve so much more.

831
00:56:18,490 --> 00:56:20,280
Sure, I got it.

832
00:56:21,680 --> 00:56:22,740
Well then...

833
00:56:23,690 --> 00:56:27,980
I won't go easy on you, Luffy.

834
00:56:28,990 --> 00:56:31,170
Of course! I wouldn't expect you to!

835
00:56:32,670 --> 00:56:34,440
Ah, hold on!

836
00:56:39,900 --> 00:56:44,580
Gramps said this was the one safe spot, right?

837
00:56:46,850 --> 00:56:51,600
Straw Hat Luffy is taking
a little break from pirating.

838
00:57:18,780 --> 00:57:20,530
Oh, right.

839
00:57:22,480 --> 00:57:23,750
This, too...

840
00:57:29,400 --> 00:57:30,320
Guys...

841
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:35,260
– Luffy!
– Luffy!

842
00:57:39,900 --> 00:57:41,660
Hey, hurry!

843
00:57:41,660 --> 00:57:43,260
Let's get started!

844
00:57:44,020 --> 00:57:45,350
Got it!

845
00:57:54,850 --> 00:57:56,890
I'm in your hands, Gramps!

846
00:57:58,600 --> 00:57:59,800
That won't do.

847
00:57:59,800 --> 00:58:02,400
Say, "Please teach me, Mr. Rayleigh"!

848
00:58:02,400 --> 00:58:04,670
No, "Professor Rayleigh"!

849
00:58:04,670 --> 00:58:05,940
Or, "Master"?

850
00:58:05,940 --> 00:58:08,320
Thanks! Please teach me, Rayleigh!

851
00:58:08,320 --> 00:58:10,850
Well, it doesn't matter.

852
00:59:43,220 --> 00:59:46,390
Zoro, Usopp, Sanji, Nami,

853
00:59:46,390 --> 00:59:49,560
Chopper, Robin, Franky, Brook...

854
00:59:50,050 --> 00:59:52,530
and Ace and Sabo!

855
00:59:52,530 --> 00:59:55,100
I promise once more...

856
00:59:55,100 --> 00:59:57,570
I'm gonna get stronger!

